    "PDPs are sometimes visualised centred at zero, depending on context.",
    "Similarly, for continuous functions, PDPs may look as follows.",
    "Figure 7 indicates the impact different percentiles of acceleration have on predicted risk premium.",
    "The black bars in the x axis indicate where the data most strongly supports the outcome, with results taken outside considered extrapolation as there are fewer data points over its range.",
    "At zero acceleration, the higher-risk premium requires further investigation as it does not adhere to the general (and expected) positive relation between risk premium and acceleration."
